= SDL_AtomicCASPtr =
Use this function to set a pointer to a new value if it is currently an old value.


== Syntax ==
```c++
SDL_bool SDL_AtomicCASPtr_(void** a,
                           void*  oldval,
                           void*  newval)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''a'''
|^a pointer to a pointer to an atomic variable^
|-
|'''oldval'''
|a pointer to the old value
|-
|'''newval'''
|a pointer to the new value
|}

== Return Value ==
Returns SDL_TRUE if the pointer was set, SDL_FALSE otherwise.

